snippet.textDisplay:
As Marvel has proven, you don't need trilogies to make success. As long as there is a COHESIVE story arc that is being used, I have no problem with stand alone, per se.

And with a wealth of stories to draw from Legends (and I know Disney could give two shits about that) it might be in their interest to at least CONSIDER some of these tales, with tweaks to fit their new universe.

Would love a story on the Jensaurri (spelled wrong, I think?) force users. I found the Coran Horn novel an intriguing and fresh story, which then went no where in terms of reproduction in the greater Legends timeline. I still weep.
snippet.textOriginal:
As Marvel has proven, you don't need trilogies to make success. As long as there is a COHESIVE story arc that is being used, I have no problem with stand alone, per se.

And with a wealth of stories to draw from Legends (and I know Disney could give two shits about that) it might be in their interest to at least CONSIDER some of these tales, with tweaks to fit their new universe.

Would love a story on the Jensaurri (spelled wrong, I think?) force users. I found the Coran Horn novel an intriguing and fresh story, which then went no where in terms of reproduction in the greater Legends timeline. I still weep.
